This implies that there is an overly strong IOD-ISMR negative correlation in the present-day simulation; i.e., pos-
itive IODs tend to be associated with an ISMR reduction, more so in models. Figure 2a shows that models with
greater IOD amplitude produce a greater IOD-ISMR negative correlation. The same analysis was conducted for
each grid point with respect to models (Fig. 2b), and the result further confirms that models with a greater IOD
amplitude tend to produce a greater IOD-ISMR negative correlation. This is seen in other IOD-affected regions,
